S&P Doesn’t Plan More Municipal Rating Cuts Linked to U.S. Downgrade

-- B y   S a r a h   F r i e r
-- 
2011-08-09T20:29:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/s-p-doesn-t-plan-any-more-municipal-ratings-cuts-linked-to-u-s-downgrade.html
Standard & Poor’s  won’t consider
further downgrades on state and local government credits
dependent on federal funding until details of the U.S. budget
are complete, Steve Murphy, managing director of U.S. public
finance for the ratings company, said in a telephone interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
